The paper deals with combinatorial models for protocol complexes in distributed computing, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also studies the topology of these complexes, which involves concepts from Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Algebraic Topology (cs.AT). The use of witness structures and simplicial complexes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study of immediate snapshot complexes as collapsible and homeomorphic to closed balls suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
